<item>
            <title>[SPARK-18200] GraphX Invalid initial capacity when running triangleCount</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-18200</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running GraphX triangle count on large-ish file results in the &quot;Invalid initial capacity&quot; error when running on Spark 2.0 (tested on Spark 2.0, 2.0.1, and 2.0.2).  You can see the results at: &lt;a href=&quot;http://bit.ly/2eQKWDN&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bit.ly/2eQKWDN&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Running the same code on Spark 1.6 and the query completes without any problems: &lt;a href=&quot;http://bit.ly/2fATO1M&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bit.ly/2fATO1M&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As well, running the GraphFrames version of this code runs as well (Spark 2.0, GraphFrames 0.2): &lt;a href=&quot;http://bit.ly/2fAS8W8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bit.ly/2fAS8W8&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reference Stackoverflow question:&lt;br/&gt;
Spark GraphX: requirement failed: Invalid initial capacity (&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/40337366/spark-graphx-requirement-failed-invalid-initial-capacity&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/40337366/spark-graphx-requirement-failed-invalid-initial-capacity&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Databricks, Ubuntu 16.04, macOS Sierra&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
